{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7798310a-b41b-40bb-9287-d706a88b5bd5","content":"No `SettingsPage.xaml` found in the working directory. Since this is a guidance question, here's how to convert your page:\n\n**Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n1. Add an `xmlns:vm` namespace pointing to your ViewModel's namespace.\n2. Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage` (or any ancestor element).\n\n**Catching binding errors at build time:**\n\nCompiled bindings (`x:DataType`) resolve property paths at compile time. If you misspell a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\nTo ensure this works:\n1. **Enable XamlC** (on by default in .NET MAUI) — confirm your `AssemblyInfo.cs` or project doesn't have `[assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Skip)]`.\n2. **Treat warnings as errors** (optional, stricter) — add to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n   ```\n\nAny typo or type mismatch in a binding path will now fail the build rather than silently failing at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0fd7b2c0-24e8-4870-baa4-64ce59107cf0","outputTokens":508,"requestId":"7FD0:21AE1A:5EC917F:6797DBB:69F15639"},"id":"834de490-9b28-4b65-9a8d-62c3edb20c2b","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:52:21.526Z","parentId":"14190cae-40e2-4c32-a497-999621b040f8"}
